Investment Philosophy  HomeAbout Our FirmInvestment PhilosophyWhy An Investor Should Own BondsSub-AdvisoryDocumentationContact  The Advantages of Working With MacroView IndependenceMacroView is independent.  This means that our sole obligation is to our clients.  We do not have quotas or corporate partners to support.  As a fee-only investment advisor, MacroView charges a percentage based on assets under management.  We do not receive commissions for products or securities that we recommend or purchase for our clients.  This structure aligns us with our clients' interests; MacroView benefits when our clients benefit.  There are no hidden fees or up-front costs.  We strive to minimize overall transaction fees and provide personal service at a competitive rate.TransparencyClients have real-time, around-the-clock access through their custodian's web site to monitor their portfolio activity and performance.Secure CustodianshipMacroView uses a very secure and transparent custodial network to ensure our clients accounts are safe.  The majority of MacroView's clients maintain their assets in THEIR individual name in a brokerage account with Charles Schwab Institutional, a division of Charles Schwab & Co., Inc. (we may, on a case-by-case basis, manage client assets at a qualified custodian other than Charles Schwab).  You don't send MacroView money.  You simply give us the right to make trades in the account on your behalf.  You can see exactly what MacroView is doing anytime by accessing your account online through your custodian.  This communication is not intended to constitute any offer or solicitation to buy or sell securities. Offers of securities or investment advisory services may be made only pursuant to appropriate offering or other disclosure documents, and only after prospective investors have had the opportunity to discuss all matters concerning the prospective investment or engagement with their advisers, the issuers of the securities or MacroView Investment Management LLC. It should be noted that past performance is not indicative of future results.7315 Wisconsin Avenue | Suite 400 West Tower | Bethesda, Maryland 20814 | 301.907.6795 | info@macroviewim.comMacroView Investment Management LLC © ALL RIGHTS RESERVED.  This communication is not intended to constitute any offer or solicitation to buy or sell securities. Offers of securities or investment advisory services may be made only pursuant to appropriate offering or other disclosure documents, and only after prospective investors have had the opportunity to discuss all matters concerning the prospective investment or engagement with their advisers, the issuers of the securities or MacroView Investment Management LLC. It should be noted that past performance is not indicative of future results.7315 Wisconsin Avenue | Suite 400 West Tower | Bethesda, Maryland 20814 | 301.907.6795 | info@macroviewim.comMacroView Investment Management LLC  © ALL RIGHTS RESERVED.    The MacroView Philosophy Achieving your financial goals requires a plan and a diversified portfolioMacroView believes that your financial goals are specific to your circumstances.  While many investors focus on stock market benchmarks, we prefer to invest in a manner that allows you to achieve your unique goals.MacroView believes diversification is essential to managing investment portfolios.  The integration of a variety of asset classes, not just investments within an asset class, is crucial to reducing risk.  The allocation of one's portfolio should be based upon the combination of individual risk and return requirements, current risk/reward valuations for each asset class, and a solid understanding of the macroeconomic climate.    This communication is not intended to constitute any offer or solicitation to buy or sell securities. Offers of securities or investment advisory services may be made only pursuant to appropriate offering or other disclosure documents, and only after prospective investors have had the opportunity to discuss all matters concerning the prospective investment or engagement with their advisers, the issuers of the securities or MacroView Investment Management LLC. It should be noted that past performance is not indicative of future results.7315 Wisconsin Avenue | Suite 400 West Tower | Bethesda, Maryland 20814 | 301.907.6795 | info@macroviewim.comMacroView Investment Management LLC  © ALL RIGHTS RESERVED.        View on Mobile
















